CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 21, 1959, pg. 9, reads: "Accent On Paris - Five of the beautiful young models who took part in D.I. fashion show-cabaret party Sunday night at the New Arena Supper Club show the extreme chic of their outfits. Left: Joyce Trower wears a beige nylon tulle gown of Balmain.  Its neckline is banded in beige lynx fur, and a faint deeper beige print is apparent in the sweeping fullness of the skirt.  It is one of the Dupont collection....-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Joyce Trower wearing light colored patterned strapless ball gown with beige lynx fur neckline, standing in front of wooden bench with tufted cushion, in New Arena Supper Club for D.I. "March" benefit for the National Foundation
